                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/micro-symfony/edit/master/knpu/container-twig.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>When you want to render a template, you'll usually extend <code>Controller</code> and it'll give
you a bunch of shortcuts, including <code>render()</code>. That's a great idea. But I'll extend
<code>ContainerAware</code> instead:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="7c6440d98a">
