</p>
<p>That gives access to the service container, but not the shortcut methods. So I can't
say <code>$this-&gt;render()</code>, but I <em>can</em> say <code>$html = $this-&gt;container-&gt;get('twig')</code> and
then call <code>render()</code> on it. Render <code>mighty_mouse/rescue.html.twig</code> and pass it a
<code>quote</code> variable. But that's just HTML - so wrap it in a <code>Response</code> and return:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="b79254a870">
    <div class="meta">
